raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  version: "1.6.0"

package:
  name: bottleneck
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/B/Bottleneck/bottleneck-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 028d46ee4b025ad9ab4d79924113816f825f62b17b87c9e1d0d8ce144a4a0e31

build:
  number: 3
  script: ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps --no-build-isolation

requirements:
  build:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - python
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - numpy
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - setuptools
    - versioneer
    - numpy
  run:
    - numpy
    - python

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - bottleneck
        - bottleneck.slow
        - bottleneck.tests
        - bottleneck.reduce
        - bottleneck.nonreduce
        - bottleneck.nonreduce_axis
        - bottleneck.move
      pip_check: true
  - requirements:
      run:
        - pytest
    script:
      - python -c "import bottleneck; bottleneck.test()"

about:
  license: BSD-2-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Fast NumPy array functions written in Cython.
  description: |
    Bottleneck is a collection of fast NumPy array functions written in
    Cython.
  homepage: https://github.com/pydata/bottleneck
  repository: https://github.com/pydata/bottleneck
  documentation: https://bottleneck.readthedocs.io

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jakirkham
    - msarahan
    - wesm
    - ocefpaf
    - qwhelan
